Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.44,0:00:07.95,Title card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,500)\fs60\pos(757.01,992)\blur1}Suitable for young children and families\N{\fscx7000}-\N{\fscx100}Recommended by the Eirin Youth Film Deliberation Council
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.39,0:00:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.07,0:00:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.24,0:00:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hear a baby crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.10,0:00:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Think somebody left a baby \Nin front of the orphanage?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.65,0:00:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.50,0:00:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There, there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.38,0:01:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear, we have to let the principal know about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.79,0:01:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, I'll go get her now!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.91,0:01:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And be quick about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.25,0:01:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we'll leave it all to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.64,0:01:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There we go. There, there.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.70,0:01:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't she a beautiful \Nbaby, Principal?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.60,0:01:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we just need \Nto give her a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.16,0:01:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Since she's the first baby we've had since I became principal,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.65,0:01:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll start with the letter 'A'.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.10,0:01:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're using the phone book to pick a name?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.90,0:01:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.18,0:01:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No, of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.16,0:01:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Abbott.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.93,0:01:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That will do nicely.\N Let's call her that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.97,0:01:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Abbott?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.79,0:02:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my. I don't think she likes that name very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.48,0:02:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Principal, what do you think of the name Judy?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.05,0:02:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.08,0:02:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it was the name \Nof my late sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.63,0:02:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.62,0:02:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.00,0:02:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be called Judy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.99,0:02:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We've decided on Judy Abbott.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.00,0:02:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,She laughed!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.43,0:02:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,She really likes the name Judy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.91,0:02:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There, good girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.81,0:02:49.98,DLL,,0,0,0,,{\be1\fs115\pos(807.08,946)\fade(0,500)}Daddy-Long-Legs{matching style with Wikipedia entry}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.81,0:02:49.98,DLL,,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur2\fs115\pos(807.08,946)\c&H7848E8&\1a&HFF&\fade(0,500)}Daddy-Long-Legs{matching style with Wikipedia entry}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.21,0:03:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{song}{この空の下のどこかで}Somewhere beneath this sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.52,0:03:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{いつか巡り合えるわ}I'm sure we'll meet someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.87,0:03:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{雲よ、わたしのおともだち}Clouds, you're my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.99,0:04:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{真っ赤な夕日の向こうには何があるの}What lies beyond \Nthat deep red sunset?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.69,0:04:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{おしえて　おしえて}Please tell me, please tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.78,0:04:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{この小さな囲いの中で}From inside this small cage...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.89,0:04:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{いつもあこがれていた　まだ見ぬ世界へ}I've always longed for \Nthe world I've never seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.54,0:04:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{この空の下のどこかで}Somewhere beneath this sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.69,0:04:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{いつか巡り合えるわ}I'm sure we'll meet someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.20,0:04:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{わたしの幸せに、わたしの幸せに}To my happiness, to my happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.68,0:05:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,There we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.27,0:05:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you all doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.91,0:05:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,A-A frog!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.60,0:05:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Freddy, catch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.92,0:05:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.66,0:05:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, get back here! \NCome on!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.53,0:06:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Save me!\N Someone, save me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.39,0:06:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is Judy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.45,0:06:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is Judy when\N you need her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.54,0:06:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The children brought yet another frog into their room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.45,0:06:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.04,0:06:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the oldest one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.79,0:06:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can't look after the children properly, then what will I do with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.86,0:06:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.67,0:06:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow is the first Wednesday of the month!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.78,0:06:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.73,0:06:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely you know what would happen if the guests saw the children acting like that?!{note}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.07,0:06:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.13,0:07:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The guests donate \Nto the orphanage,{note}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.29,0:07:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so we all have to be on our best behavior when they're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.28,0:07:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.58,0:07:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And that goes double for you. You've been here for 17 years, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.10,0:07:20.46,Default,,30,30,0,,{\fscx95}When most people finish middle school, \Nthey go to high school and then start working.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.17,0:07:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But you are being allowed to attend the village high school as a special exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.21,0:07:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd best remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.91,0:07:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I appreciate it, I really do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.96,0:07:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That matter aside, the principal has something important to discuss with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.03,0:07:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Three months from now, you'll graduate high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.60,0:07:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We will discuss your future with the rest of the benefactors tomorrow.{note}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.03,0:07:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,My future?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.83,0:07:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In my opinion, you are free to work here, should you wish to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.39,0:08:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But we must ask our benefactors.{note}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.57,0:08:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.34,0:08:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.17,0:08:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm to work, I'd like to do it somewhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.06,0:08:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to work \Nsomewhere else?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.28,0:08:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.82,0:08:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to try working \Nin the outside world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.25,0:08:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.11,0:08:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,A child raised in an orphanage knows nothing of the troubles of the real world!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.27,0:08:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I intend to know of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.95,0:08:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think you understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.97,0:08:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you know how hard life will be outside of the orphanage?!{talking like she's done a stint in prison}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.34,0:08:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Does she, Principal?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.69,0:08:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, we'll come to a decision with our benefactors tomorrow.{note}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.72,0:08:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But I will let them know what you want to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.25,0:09:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.34,0:09:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Judy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.07,0:09:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{broken frames?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.47,0:09:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm sorry, Judy.\N- I'm sorry, Judy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.08,0:09:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry about what?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.74,0:09:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Y'know, about the frog.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.08,0:09:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.93,0:09:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I only got told off a little, \Nso we're okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.47,0:09:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But remember, tomorrow is \Nthe first Wednesday of the month,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.22,0:09:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,so the benefactors \Nwill be coming over.{note}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.34,0:09:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.42,0:09:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, not this again!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.45,0:09:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Freddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.81,0:09:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you on \Nyour best behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.85,0:09:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't behave,\N I'll be given another earful!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.32,0:09:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You got it, Judy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.90,0:09:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, everyone, \Nback to their rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.94,0:09:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Wednesday, Wednesday, \Nblue Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.81,0:10:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{今日は第一水曜日}Today is the first \NWednesday of the month.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.71,0:10:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{評議員の皆様が馬車や車でやってくる }The members of the board come riding in carriages and cars.{note}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.22,0:10:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Wednesday, Wednesday, \Nblue Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.84,0:10:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{みんな一日いい子になって}Everyone has to \Nbe good all day long.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.40,0:10:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{朝から晩まだ大変なんだ}From morning till night,\N it's such hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.02,0:10:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{床はつるつる、窓はぴかぴか、椅子も机もほこりをなくし}Floors glisten, windows sparkle, every chair and desk wiped clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.72,0:10:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{ベッドメイクにシャワーにシャンプー、服はのりつき、ギンガムチェック}Beds made, showered and shampooed, clothes starched, gingham checks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.53,0:10:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Wednesday, Wednesday, \Nblue Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.50,0:10:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{月に一度のこの日がなけりゃ}If not for this day \Nthat comes once a month,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.42,0:10:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{ここのくらしもまんざらじゃないのに}life here wouldn't \Nbe so bad at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.83,0:10:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{ああ　ああ　いやだな水曜日}Ah, ah, how I hate Wednesdays.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.39,0:11:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{水曜日なんて、こなきゃいいのに}I wish Wednesdays \Nwould never come.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.07,0:11:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{今日は第一水曜日}Today is the first \NWednesday of the month.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.70,0:11:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{評議員の皆様に月に一度のごあいさつ。}The members of the board pay us their monthly visit.{note}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.43,0:11:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Wednesday, Wednesday,\N blue Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.03,0:11:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{みんな一日お行儀良くし}Everyone has to mind their manners all day long.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.42,0:11:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{おまけに食事も出さなきゃならぬ}And on top of that,\N we must serve the meals.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.05,0:11:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{返事はきはき、はい先生}Answer promptly. "Yes, sir."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.17,0:11:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{姿勢正しく、いいえ先生}Stand up straight. "No, sir."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.97,0:11:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{ボタンは全部きちんとはめて、けんか泣き虫おしゃべりだめよ}Buttons fastened tight, no crying, \Nno squabbling, and no chattering.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.47,0:11:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Wednesday, Wednesday, \Nblue Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.52,0:11:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{勇気出して耐えてしまう}Be brave and just endure it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.94,0:11:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{明日が来れば忘れてしまおう}When tomorrow comes,\N we'll forget it all anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.53,0:12:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{ああ　ああ　いやだな水曜日}Ah, ah, how I hate Wednesdays.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.93,0:12:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{水曜日なんて、こなきゃいいのに}I wish Wednesdays \Nwould never come.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.66,0:12:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There are a number of things I wish to discuss with you all today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.65,0:12:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,First on the agenda...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.20,0:12:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is our oldest orphan,\N Judy Abbott.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.79,0:13:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.29,0:13:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.62,0:13:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you so spaced out?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.24,0:13:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The principal \Nwants to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.87,0:13:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Again?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.69,0:13:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I make a mess \Nof something again?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.16,0:13:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought we were all well-behaved in front of our guests.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.79,0:13:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You were, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.98,0:13:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But you should really \Nhurry up and see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.22,0:13:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, I'll go and see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.93,0:14:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.05,0:14:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You wanted to see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.23,0:14:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I did indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.31,0:14:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, take a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.49,0:14:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.70,0:15:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see the \Nman who just left?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.24,0:15:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I only saw him from behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.56,0:15:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That man is the richest \Namong our guests,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.42,0:15:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and has donated a lot of\N money to the orphanage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.75,0:15:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.12,0:15:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But his name is kept secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.22,0:15:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's how he \Nwants to keep it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.93,0:15:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.16,0:15:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Charles Penton and Henry Fritz, who used to live here,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.89,0:15:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,only went to university \Nbecause of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.51,0:15:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted to offer a scholarship to \Na promising young boy this year as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.17,0:15:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that nice?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.89,0:15:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the matter of your \Nfuture came up during our meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.91,0:15:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.98,0:15:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So that the benefactors could get to know what kind of person you are,{note}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.13,0:15:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Mrs. Pritchard read aloud a poem you had written, one called "Wednesday."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.56,0:16:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of poem was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.54,0:16:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm terribly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.71,0:16:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Making fun of the very people \Nwho had been so good to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.59,0:16:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's nothing \Nto be proud of.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.47,0:16:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.65,0:16:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.23,0:16:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The man who just left seems to take quite \Nan interest in that rude writing of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.35,0:16:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And has offered to \Nsend you to university.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.59,0:16:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,T-To university?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.98,0:16:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Sit down, Judy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.47,0:16:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.00,0:16:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But he really wants to send me to university?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.97,0:16:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm as surprised as you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.65,0:16:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But he's a very \Nidiosyncratic{let me use big words} man.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.51,0:16:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that your very 'unique' manner of writing showed talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.42,0:16:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And set up a plan for you to become a writer in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.49,0:16:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,A writer?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.05,0:16:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a novelist?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.68,0:16:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.99,0:16:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Me, a writer?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.45,0:16:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I could...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.35,0:17:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So, shall I cancel \Nthe university plans?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.25,0:17:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.63,0:17:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.22,0:17:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Please let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.46,0:17:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is one condition for \Nhim to put you through university.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.96,0:17:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That is for you to write a letter to him once per month.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.26,0:17:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.19,0:17:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that all he wants in \Nplace of the money?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.61,0:17:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not quite.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.82,0:17:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Had your parents been alive, you'd tell \Nthem of how your school life was faring.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.39,0:17:49.17,Default,,30,30,0,,{\fscx95}Like how your studies were going, what \Nyou did with your friends, that kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.17,0:17:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, would you be able \Nto tell me his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.22,0:17:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm to send them a letter, \Nit has to be addressed to someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.19,0:17:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Griggs' Law Office will suffice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.61,0:18:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Griggs?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.94,0:18:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He happens to be a legal advisor to our benefactor.{note}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.45,0:18:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Griggs will be coming \Nto town before you leave,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.48,0:18:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and he'll take care of \Nthe arrangements for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.46,0:18:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You should be thankful for having \Nrun into such good fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.75,0:18:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.19,0:18:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Farewell!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.44,0:18:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- Farewell!\N- Take care!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.24,0:18:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- Judy, you forgot this!\N- Bye-bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.02,0:18:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh my.\N- See you later, Judy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.06,0:18:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.13,0:18:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.86,0:18:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- See you later!\N- Take care!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.16,0:19:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{心は青空はれて}My heart is a clear blue sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.43,0:19:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{うきうきしているわ}I'm in high spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.79,0:19:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{だれでもいい聞いてほしいこの胸のときめき}I want anyone at all to hear this flutter in my chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.65,0:19:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{ギンガムチェック副を着た、そばかす娘だったわたし}I was just a freckled girl in a gingham checked dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.39,0:19:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{まさか大学にいけるなんて}I never dreamed I'd \Nget to go to university.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.14,0:19:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{バラ色に染まる見知らぬ世界が広がる}An unfamiliar world, rosy with promise, spreads before me.{not sure how best to deal with the whole "bara-iro" - didn't want to go "rose-tinted"}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.98,0:19:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{まぶしいほどうれしくなり、ほほえみがこぼれるわ}I'm so dazzlingly happy, \NI can't help but smile!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.41,0:19:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{だけどちょっとまって}But wait just a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.78,0:19:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{なんだか心奥のほう}Somewhere deep \Ninside my heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.27,0:19:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{ちょっぴり重たいものがある}there's something that's \Nweighing me down.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.73,0:20:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{せけん知らずこのジュディ}I, Judy, who knows \Nnothing of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.23,0:20:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{ほんとにひとりで大丈夫なの}will I really be all \Nright on my own?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.81,0:20:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{えいいジュディ}Come on now, Judy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.69,0:20:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{くよくよしたってはじまらぬ}Worrying won't \Nget you anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.57,0:20:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{当たってくだけろ何ごとも}Throw yourself in and \Nbreak through anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.11,0:20:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{元気出しなよ、さあジュディ}Cheer up now, \Ncome on, Judy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.79,0:20:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{新しい私の旅だから}This is the journey \Nof a brand new me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.51,0:20:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{がんばれがんばれジュディ　くよくよせずに}Go for it, go for it, Judy. \NDon't you worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.01,0:20:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{がんばれジュディ、まけるなジュディ、元気を出しな}Go for it, Judy. Don't give up, Judy. \NKeep your spirits high!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.07,0:20:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{がんばれがんばれジュディ　いいことだけを}Go for it, go for it, Judy. \NThink only of good things.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.90,0:21:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{がんばれジュディ、まけるなジュディ、信じていきな}Go for it, Judy. Don't give up, Judy. \NBelieve in yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.96,0:21:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My dear benefactor, \NI've been thinking about you a lot.{note}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.69,0:21:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are only two \Nthings I know about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.10,0:21:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Even blessed with imagination, \Nthere isn't much for me to go off.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.74,0:21:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Number one, you're wealthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.15,0:21:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Number two, you're tall.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.79,0:21:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did think of calling you Mr. Moneybags,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.79,0:21:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'd feel bad if your \Nfortune ever changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.05,0:21:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So I've decided to call you \NDaddy-Long-Legs instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.22,0:21:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't take it personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.97,0:22:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.10,0:22:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.89,0:22:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, which way \Nis the university?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.70,0:22:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, are you a \Nnew student as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.20,0:22:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.16,0:22:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So am I! \NWhy don't we go together?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.08,0:22:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we close by?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.56,0:22:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be better \Nto go by carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.74,0:22:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,By carriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.70,0:23:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard it's traditional for new students at Walston{looks like they nicked the name from the film adaption} to arrive by carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.58,0:23:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.90,0:23:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.67,0:23:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, get in.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.33,0:23:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Judy Abbott.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.15,0:23:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Sally McBride. A pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.38,0:23:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The pleasure is all mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.97,0:23:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since I got into university, I thought \Nabout what kind of person I'd meet first.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.98,0:23:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you know \Nanybody here?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.00,0:23:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No, what about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.62,0:23:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Me neither. \NHow about we be friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.82,0:24:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.45,0:24:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,"And by some coincidence, we even \Nended up sharing the same room."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.74,0:24:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,"It's three people to a room, so we're \Nwith someone called Susan Pendleton."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.02,0:24:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,"Susan comes from a well-to-do family in New York...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.14,0:24:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and has a very prim and proper air about her."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.02,0:24:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,"I don't think I'll be friends with her as quickly as I was with Sally."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.27,0:24:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.88,0:25:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, all of your \Nclothes are so pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.67,0:25:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, these old things?{liberal idc}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.20,0:25:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you pick these yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.69,0:25:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.05,0:25:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, can I borrow this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.27,0:25:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.62,0:25:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I could buy \Nclothes like these.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.35,0:25:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet your parents dote\N on you all the time, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.01,0:25:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have any parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.45,0:25:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.43,0:25:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if they were around, they wouldn't \Nhave the money for things like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.89,0:25:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But a very kind person got me \Nthem so I could attend university.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.82,0:25:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.93,0:25:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.47,0:25:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to come downstairs \Nto the tearoom with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.68,0:25:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We can get acquainted \Nover a cup of tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.38,0:26:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.39,0:26:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't bring myself to tell them \Nthat I was raised in an orphanage.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.84,0:26:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard the cake \Nhere is wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.31,0:26:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.16,0:26:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- Congratulations!\N- Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.31,0:26:38.03,Default,,30,30,0,,{ここはうるわしき乙女の花園、知性さずける学びの庭よ}{\fscx95}This is a lovely garden of maidens, \Na courtyard of learning that grants us wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.03,0:26:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{けれど新米の皆様方にはまるで地獄の責苦のようよ}But for you brand new students, it feels like you're in Hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.87,0:27:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{朝起きてから眠るまでベルカラベルまで区切られて息つくひまもありゃしない}From waking up to going to bed, bells mark off every moment, no time even to breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.22,0:27:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{どっさり本を読まされてそのうえ図書館待っている}You’re made to read piles of books, and then the library is waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.19,0:27:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{へとへとになりスケジュール}Dead tired from the schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.21,0:27:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{こなしたとたんに　はい！消燈}The moment you finish it, it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.44,0:27:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{こなしたとたんに　はい！消燈}Lights out!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.79,0:27:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{それじゃ恋するひまもない、上級生にいびられて}There's no time to fall in love, \Nand the upperclassmen pick on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.85,0:27:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{先生からはどなられて同級生はとよりない}Teachers yell at you and your classmates are no help there.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.04,0:27:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{ああ、ああ、あわれな私たち}Ah, ah, how pitiful we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.92,0:27:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{わたしもあなたも大学生}You and I alike, \Nuniversity students.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.56,0:27:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{けれどみんなさん、慌てないで}But, everyone, don't panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.48,0:27:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{要領ひとつのみこめば}Once you get the hang of things,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.19,0:27:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{ここほど住みよいとこはない、うるさいおやじのお説教}there's nowhere more comfortable and there are no lectures from your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.15,0:28:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{買い物野好きのおふくろのやぼな手伝い何もない}You're never forced to go shopping with your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.13,0:28:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{本がコーヒーに化けだって}Even if books turn into coffee,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.27,0:28:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{そんなの誰もしるもんか}who's going to care anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.59,0:28:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{ああ、ああ、楽しい大学生}Ah, ah, happy university students.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.50,0:28:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{住めば都とはこのことよ}"Home is where you make it" really says it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.85,0:29:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome, Mrs. Pritchard.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.18,0:29:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, I know \Nyou must be busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.90,0:29:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, take a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.79,0:29:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I take it you're worried \Nabout Judy Abbott?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.35,0:29:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.48,0:29:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I was wondering how she \Nwas getting on at university.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.95,0:29:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,While I haven't seen her in person, \Nshe seems to be enjoying herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.25,0:29:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,At least, that's how \NI interpret her letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.97,0:29:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.71,0:29:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I must say, that girl's letters \Nare quite the interesting read.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.32,0:29:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy-Long-Legs of all things.\NDaddy-Long-Legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.74,0:29:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy-Long-Legs? \NWhat's that about?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.44,0:29:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know how it came about, \Nbut ever since she left for university,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.79,0:29:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,she's given him the name of Daddy-Long-Legs in her letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.40,0:29:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,My, what a rude \Nthing to call someone!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.36,0:29:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.13,0:30:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He found it rather amusing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.05,0:30:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... is it always to \NDaddy-Long-Legs?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.87,0:30:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, she was supposed to\N send one letter per month,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.94,0:30:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but she's been sending about one per week so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.25,0:30:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, she always did have \Na thing for literature.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.94,0:30:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, has he been \Nreading her letters?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.59,0:30:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, indeed. Of course he's been reading them.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.48,0:30:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since he went to France,\N they've been waiting here for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.69,0:30:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So, would you like to hear one?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.61,0:30:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, if you wouldn't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.63,0:30:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind in the slightest.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.50,0:30:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth be told, I also look forward to getting her letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.42,0:31:01.03,Default,,30,30,0,,{\fscx95}"These letters are a little one-sided, so I was wondering if you could answer a few things."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.65,0:31:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I would appreciate it if you could answer these questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.01,0:31:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you an older gentleman?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.06,0:31:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Or are you younger perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.14,0:31:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you bald?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.50,0:31:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Or do you have a \Nlittle bit of hair left?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.68,0:31:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I look forward to \Nhearing back from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.36,0:31:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,My, what do \Nyou think of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.90,0:31:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, aren't they rather\N interesting to read?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.87,0:31:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, this is Griggs' Law Office. Yes, that's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.51,0:31:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's from Daddy-Long-Legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.50,0:31:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.89,0:31:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing I have is that \Nletter for your eyes only.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.29,0:31:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.23,0:31:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, there are two more \Nletters from Judy Abbott.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.93,0:31:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If you could just \Nwait a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.34,0:32:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And another one \Nhas just arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.57,0:32:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall I read it to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.25,0:32:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well, just a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.06,0:32:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,"Dear, Daddy-Long-Legs."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.24,0:32:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like you really are Daddy-Long-Legs now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.01,0:32:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes, I'll read it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.35,0:32:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'm currently in hospital."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.45,0:32:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,"I've got both tonsillitis, influenza, and probably a few other things too."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.73,0:32:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh Lord...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.23,0:32:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you \Nfeeling now, Judy?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.66,0:32:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, \NI feel much better now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.28,0:32:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A present came for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.10,0:32:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, I wonder who it's from.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.35,0:32:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a letter attached.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.71,0:33:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,"How are you feeling?"
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.79,0:33:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,"I hope you get better, Judy. I look forward to many more letters - Daddy-Long-Legs."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.85,0:33:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.98,0:33:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,My, it's beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.39,0:33:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy, are you \Nfeeling better now?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.22,0:33:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Sally, Susan!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.18,0:33:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You look a lot better!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.49,0:33:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my! \NWhat beautiful roses!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.00,0:33:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet these cost a fortune!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.25,0:33:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, who sent you these?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.29,0:33:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,R-Remember that \Nman I told you about?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.59,0:33:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,"I look forward to many more letters - Daddy-Long-Legs."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.77,0:33:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.89,0:33:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.44,0:34:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,"Daddy-Long-Legs, this is the first time I've been given a present in hospital."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.78,0:34:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,"I was so happy, \NI could've cried."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.27,0:34:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,"Thank you so very much."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.49,0:34:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,"And, now that I know you read my letters,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.15,0:34:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you look forward \Nto even more of them!"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.60,0:34:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.03,0:34:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you help me?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.15,0:34:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,With what?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.49,0:34:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You have got a gap \Nbetween classes, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.41,0:34:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.50,0:35:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was going to \Npractice basketball.{bitch gonna practice her dunks}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.63,0:35:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you skip \Npractice for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.97,0:35:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm as surprised as you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.94,0:35:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I never thought Uncle Jervis{stupid name} would come and visit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.49,0:35:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What did he do that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.99,0:35:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He said he had a meeting \Nto attend in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.25,0:35:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it reminded \Nhim I go to school here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.38,0:35:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you want \Nme to meet him?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.35,0:35:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be fine. \NIt's only for an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.09,0:35:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And an hour will fly by when you're \Ngiving him a tour of the university.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.71,0:35:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.63,0:35:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, there we have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.71,0:35:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.57,0:35:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to keep \Nyou waiting, Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.49,0:35:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.13,0:36:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Allow me to introduce you. \NThis is Judy Abbott, my roommate.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.98,0:36:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Jervis Pendleton.{Jee, I wonder if this guy is daddy long legs}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.79,0:36:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,A pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.26,0:36:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,A pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.97,0:36:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Uncle, Judy will show you around the university. I've got classes to attend.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.70,0:36:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.43,0:36:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll meet up with \Nyou both later, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.79,0:36:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.57,0:36:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Ms. Abbott, would \Nyou care to show me around?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.29,0:36:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Oh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.14,0:36:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.97,0:36:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When Susan mentioned her uncle, \NI assumed he'd be much older.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.94,0:36:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm already 33 years old.{and she's like 18, bro's on thin ice}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.55,0:36:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So I am old compared to you.{yet, he still a predator}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.29,0:36:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not. You're \Nnot old in the slightest.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.86,0:37:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,"Daddy-Long-Legs... would you \Nlike to visit one day as well?"
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.85,0:37:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'm very good at \Nshowing people around."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.55,0:37:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,"I used to do it all the time \Nat the orphanage, after all."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.72,0:37:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,"I think it would be wonderful \Nto show you around."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.94,0:37:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,"I showed Susan's \Nuncle around today."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.27,0:37:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,"He's from the esteemed Pendleton family, but he was very easy to talk to."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.68,0:37:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,"I keep thinking if this is what you would've been like 20 years ago."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.53,0:37:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the university hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.07,0:37:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I was here not too long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.06,0:37:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, are you unwell?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.81,0:37:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.73,0:37:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So I see. \NYou seem rather lively.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.77,0:37:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm starting to \Nget a little tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.25,0:37:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there anywhere we can \Nget a cup of tea around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.83,0:37:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There is, but Susan's class\N should be ending soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.47,0:38:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't we go \Nand meet her?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.84,0:38:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it doesn't bother me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.85,0:38:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,There are other things \NI want to talk to you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.69,0:38:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how about that cup of tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.83,0:38:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Since it's the end\N of the month,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.48,0:38:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,most people have used up their \Npocket money, so it's really quiet here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.08,0:38:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you used all \Nof yours up too?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.33,0:38:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't usually, but I \Nbought a book this month.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.90,0:38:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I don't have a \Npenny to my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.71,0:38:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If you wouldn't mind telling me, \Nwhat kind of book is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.73,0:38:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the works of Shakespeare.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.38,0:38:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely they have \NShakespeare in the library?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.45,0:38:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They do.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.68,0:38:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But I just had to have\N a copy of my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.44,0:38:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.36,0:39:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's almost \Ntime for my train.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.88,0:39:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.57,0:39:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Abbott, please \Ngive Susan my regards.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.28,0:39:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have to head home.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.14,0:39:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew we shouldn't\N have gone for tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.50,0:39:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you made this whole \Nordeal rather enjoyable.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.86,0:39:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy, where did \NUncle Jervis go?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.71,0:39:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.78,0:39:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that Uncle Jervis is considered a \Nbit of an oddball in the Pendleton family,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.33,0:39:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but he came all the way here to see me, \Nand didn't even speak to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.95,0:39:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, he spent all \Nday talking to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.58,0:39:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.94,0:40:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I should've paid more\N attention to the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.13,0:40:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Uncle Jervis is a rather \Ndifficult man, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.15,0:40:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I didn't feel that way. I mean, \Nwe talked about all sorts of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.62,0:40:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Time went by so fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.42,0:40:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.98,0:40:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I've only spoken with \Nmy uncle a handful of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.74,0:40:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,There are rumors in my family that he hates \Nwomen, and that's why he hasn't married.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.23,0:40:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.16,0:40:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, hey! \NThese were delivered to us!{truncated a little}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.54,0:40:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.36,0:40:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They look like chocolates.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.87,0:40:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They came from \Nthe chocolate shop in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.86,0:40:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, who are they from?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.30,0:40:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see... they're \Nfrom Jervis Pendleton.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.80,0:40:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.87,0:40:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,"To my beloved niece, Susan, \Nand her two delightful roommates."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.29,0:40:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,"To Judy and Sally McBride, a little thank \Nyou for today's visit - Jervis Pendleton."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.71,0:40:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Uncle, that's so like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.08,0:40:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's even addressed to me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.25,0:40:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you talk to \Nmy uncle about Sally?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.47,0:41:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.32,0:41:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how did he \Nknow about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.26,0:41:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure someone \Nelse must've told him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.44,0:41:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, let's eat some.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.71,0:41:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- They look delicious!\N- They look delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.35,0:41:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,"Susan said Mr. Pendleton \Nwas a little odd,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.97,0:41:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but I didn't think \Nanything of the sort."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.76,0:41:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,"If I'm being honest with you, that was \Nthe first time I'd ever spoken with a man."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.73,0:41:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,"That's not to say that speaking to \Nthe visitors at the orphanage was easy,{note}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.29,0:41:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but this was the first time I'd had \Na proper conversation with a young man."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.81,0:41:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,"To Daddy-Long-Legs, from Judy."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.89,0:42:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,"P.S. You're more than welcome to come to the university as well."
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.53,0:42:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,"I would love to show you around."
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.02,0:42:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I returned to the orphanage over the summer break for the first time in a year. {not sure if I should treat these as quotes from her letters}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.98,0:42:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Ann is unwell, so Ms. Rivette has asked me to come tend to the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.03,0:42:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's Judy!\N- She's back!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.34,0:42:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You've grown so much, Freddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.93,0:42:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- Freddy!\N- What a relief!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.32,0:43:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{空を横切る虹を見る時、七色の橋を渡れたらな}When you see a rainbow, you wish you \Ncould cross that seven-colored bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.20,0:43:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{。。。て思うでしょう}That's what you think, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.20,0:43:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{白い翼で大空高く、はばたく鳥になってみたいな}With white wings, soaring high in the open sky, you want to be a bird in flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.90,0:43:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{。。。て思うでしょう}That's what you think, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.00,0:43:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{Pそれがイマジネーション、それさえあれば見えない世界が見えてくる}That's imagination, with just that, \Ninvisible worlds come into view.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.51,0:43:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{だからイマジネーション、それさえあれば退屈しているひまはない}As long as you have imagination, \Nthere's no time to ever be bored.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.22,0:43:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagination. (Imagination.)
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.20,0:43:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{どんな時でもイマジネーション}Any time at all, imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.70,0:43:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagination. (Imagination.)
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.04,0:44:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{大切なのはイマジネーション}What matters most\N is imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.93,0:44:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{あなたもわたしも　イ、イ、イマジネーション}For you and I as well.\N I-I-Imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.05,0:44:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{もしもあなたがゆううつならばステキな明日を夢見てごらん}If you're feeling gloomy, \Ntry dreaming of a wonderful tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.03,0:44:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{。。。ね楽しいでしょう}That's fun, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.45,0:44:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{もしも涙がこぼれ来たらゆかいな事件を思い出すのよ}If tears should start to fall, \Nremember something happy.{avoiding "yukai na jiken" atm - can't think of a nice way to word stuff idk}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.86,0:44:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{。。。ねおかしいでしょう}It's funny, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.35,0:44:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{それがイマジネーションそれさえあれば不可能を可能に変えられる}That's imagination, with just that, \Nyou can turn the impossible into possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.09,0:44:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{だからイマジネーションそれさえあれば金持王様めじゃないわ}So imagination, with just that, \Nyou don't need to be a rich king.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.59,0:44:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagination. (Imagination.)
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.15,0:45:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{誰に会ってもイマジネーション}Whoever you meet,\N imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.60,0:45:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagination. (Imagination.)
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.07,0:45:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{愛のハートでイマジネーション}With a heart full of love,\N imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.94,0:45:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{あなたもわたしも　イ、イ、イマジネーション}For you and I as well.\N I-I-Imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.84,0:45:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{あなたもわたしも　イ、イ、イマジネーション}For you and I as well.\N I-I-Imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.94,0:45:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.36,0:45:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.79,0:45:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Judy, you want to come \Nto my house over Christmas?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.67,0:45:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,To your house?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.89,0:45:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to stay here last \NChristmas, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.24,0:45:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So, wanna come over?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.61,0:45:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You really don't mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.36,0:45:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.02,0:46:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,As it happens, \NI've already asked my parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.68,0:46:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I said I might be bringing \Na friend over for Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.37,0:46:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.81,0:46:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Susan, what happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.62,0:46:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a centipede.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.93,0:46:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I-It fell from the roof \Nonto my desk!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.40,0:46:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Not again...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.34,0:46:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's... \Nnothing on her desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.51,0:46:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, there is!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.67,0:46:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, there it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.15,0:46:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's huge!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.70,0:46:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Why'd a centipede have \Nto show up now of all times?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.22,0:46:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my slipper!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.21,0:46:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Sally!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.23,0:46:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Throw that slipper away!\NI won't wear that ever again!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.98,0:46:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay, it'll only \Nbe on the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.92,0:46:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No way, those things \Ngive me the creeps.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.69,0:47:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll head back to my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.37,0:47:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope there isn't \Nanother one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.14,0:47:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's gone now.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.85,0:47:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy's writing a novel,\N isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.51,0:47:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It sure looks that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.90,0:47:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The school magazine is accepting \Nadmissions for stories, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.31,0:47:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And she'll be aiming\N for first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.70,0:47:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You never know, \NJudy might just do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.14,0:47:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right, \Nshe is a rather good writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.02,0:47:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,"Dear, Daddy-Long-Legs,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.51,0:47:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I've finally finished my novel."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.49,0:47:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,"If I remember correctly, \Nyou did say I'd end up being a writer."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.35,0:48:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,"Daddy-Long-Legs, I've been invited to Sally's house over Christmas."
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.41,0:48:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,"Sally's home reminded me of the orphanage."
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.12,0:48:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,"I was so curious about how it would look on the inside."
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.19,0:48:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,"And it was just how \NI imagined it."
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.34,0:48:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy, would you \Nlike another?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.89,0:48:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.41,0:48:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Sally, I'm home!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.89,0:48:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.83,0:48:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother, I've brought \NJudy with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.47,0:48:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.62,0:48:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my brother, Tommy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.21,0:48:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a fourth-year \Nstudent at Princeton.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.71,0:48:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Judy Abbott.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.02,0:48:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,My sister has told \Nme all about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.20,0:48:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,She says you're \Nquite the writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.78,0:48:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.67,0:48:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy... is writing a novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.20,0:48:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that I'd like to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.20,0:48:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it will be in the school \Nmagazine, so I'll send you a copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.91,0:48:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Sally, that's not happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.59,0:49:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way my \Nnovel will get picked.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.59,0:49:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to be more \Nconfident in yourself, Judy.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.81,0:49:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, by the way, Father, I've prepared \Nall the presents for the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.22,0:49:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.13,0:49:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,On Christmas Eve,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.95,0:49:21.03,Default,,30,30,0,,{\fscx95}we go to give presents to the children of the people who work in my father's factory.{unless this is child labor and I've misinterpreted}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.22,0:49:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You should come see \Nthe Christmas tree as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.81,0:49:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, can Judy \Ngive us a hand too?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.77,0:49:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that's a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.75,0:49:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{note - defo not guessing}{そりがすますとぶように　そりを走る???}...the sleigh glides on by...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.77,0:49:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{はやてを切り　雪をつき}Cutting through the wind, cutting through the snow...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.86,0:49:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{たのしく歌を　うたいながら - fuck knows on the end}Singing merry songs, \Nbells ringing all around!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.54,0:49:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{ヘイ！ジングルベル ジングルベル そりはゆく}Hey! Jingle bells, jingle bells, \Nthe sleigh glides on by.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.07,0:49:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{今夜のひづめの　ひびきをゆかいに}Tonight the sound of hooves rings out with cheer!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.32,0:49:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{ヘイ！ジングルベル ジングルベル そりはゆく}Hey! Jingle bells, jingle bells, \Nthe sleigh glides on by.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.30,0:50:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{歌を歌えば　心は飛ぶよ}When we sing a song, \Nour hearts take flight!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.07,0:50:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.68,0:50:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- Wow! \N- It's Santa!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.52,0:50:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, we've got \Npresents for all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.51,0:50:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All in a line now!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.78,0:50:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The smallest kids first! \NHey, no pushing!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.43,0:50:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy, give me a hand here! Judy!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.16,0:50:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.10,0:50:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,All in a line now!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.25,0:50:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a dolly.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.56,0:50:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- Don't forget me!\N- Thank you, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.73,0:50:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but this present \Nis from Santa.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.05,0:50:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, this book \Nlooks interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.46,0:50:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.86,0:50:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,"It was a very \Nstrange feeling."
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.82,0:50:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,"Was this what it felt like to be a benefactor at John Grier's Orphanage?"{note}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.83,0:50:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,"They used to give us presents \Nwhile looking at us with pity."{note -  not keen on "pity" for nasakebukai}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.14,0:51:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,"But what I hated most of \Nall was them rubbing our hair."
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.80,0:51:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,"It really is a strange feeling."
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.64,0:51:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,"For Judy the orphan to be giving presents to children of all things."
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.51,0:51:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Silent night, holy night.{let's pretend it's that}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.75,0:51:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The stars are shining.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.89,0:51:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The child of salvation...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.66,0:51:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,rests within his mother's arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.22,0:51:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- Goodbye! Goodbye!\N- Bye-bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.41,0:51:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- Goodbye!\N- Goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.61,0:51:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.03,0:51:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- Bye-bye!\N- Bye-bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.61,0:51:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.11,0:51:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on now.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.98,0:51:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- Goodbye!\N- Bye-bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.87,0:51:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Brother, how about we \Nthrow a dance party for Judy?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.19,0:52:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I was planning \Non that already.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.17,0:52:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,As it happens, I've already spoken \Nto Mother and Father about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.91,0:52:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.55,0:52:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy, we're hosting a party for \Nyou the day after tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.35,0:52:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What? All for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.28,0:52:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.70,0:52:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,She's even brought her very \Nown white evening dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.29,0:52:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy's a pretty girl, \Nso I'm sure white will suit you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.82,0:52:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,"I wore the white evening \Ndress you sent me...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.14,0:52:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the white gloves...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.65,0:52:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the white shoes and \Ndanced with Tommy."
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.74,0:53:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,"They all said I looked beautiful."
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.52,0:53:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,"Deep down, I thought the same thing, so it made me feel happy."
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.79,0:53:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'm so terribly vain, aren't I?"
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.70,0:53:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,"I even invited Tommy \Nto the university festival."
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.53,0:53:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.82,0:53:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Sally?\N You seem in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.37,0:53:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I need to find Judy.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.25,0:53:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're looking for her, she should \Nbe in the teahouse with a guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.99,0:53:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, right! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.57,0:53:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And Susan's with her too!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.56,0:54:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that was delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.07,0:54:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Judy!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.34,0:54:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.86,0:54:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Sally. This is my uncle,\N Jervis Pendleton.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.63,0:54:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Sally McBride, \Nmy roommate.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.83,0:54:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-Thank you \Nfor the chocolates.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.41,0:54:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, think nothing of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.63,0:54:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, hey, Judy!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.47,0:54:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got big news!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.78,0:54:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.46,0:54:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing's wrong at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.85,0:54:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You won first place!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.83,0:54:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Your novel! It's going to be published in the school magazine!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.82,0:54:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew yours\N would get first place!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.53,0:55:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I overheard Ms. Morris, \Nthe editor, talking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.34,0:55:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Though, it won't be \Nofficial until tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.78,0:55:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that great, Judy?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.33,0:55:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I got first place? \NI can hardly believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.75,0:55:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They said that you'll be \Nthe first ever second-year to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.53,0:55:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.55,0:55:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If you'll allow me to congratulate \Nyou too, Miss Abbott.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.98,0:55:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Mr. Pendleton.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.97,0:55:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.99,0:55:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, call me Jervis.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.90,0:55:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And may I call \Nyou Judy in return?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.95,0:55:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well, Jervis.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.73,0:55:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that's much better.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.16,0:55:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.40,0:55:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Uncle, will you make \Nit in time for the train?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.02,0:55:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.36,0:55:54.64,Default,,30,30,0,,{\fscx95}Well, if I am talking with three pretty young \Nladies, there's no way I could hurry home.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.64,0:55:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, Uncle, \Nyou should stay a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.52,0:55:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If I may say something.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.59,0:56:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope I'm not being \Na nuisance, ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.94,0:56:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.18,0:56:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course you aren't.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.67,0:56:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.05,0:56:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I suppose I'll help \Nmyself to another sandwich.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.29,0:56:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, that reminds me, Judy.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.99,0:56:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You said you bought a copy of \Nthe works of Shakespeare, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.85,0:56:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.99,0:56:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hamlet is being shown at \Nthe Strong Theater in New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.12,0:56:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard it's rather good.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.24,0:56:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so? \NIt sounds lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.23,0:56:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you two like \NShakespeare too?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.10,0:56:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.82,0:56:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.51,0:56:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, it's decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.89,0:56:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,"Dear, Daddy-Long-Legs,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.93,0:56:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,last Friday, Sally, Susan, \Nand myself went to New York."
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.00,0:56:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,"Jervis took us all to see Hamlet."
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.90,0:57:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,"Susan stayed at her own home, but Sally and I stayed at the Sheraton Hotel."
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.69,0:57:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,"It's my first time seeing a play, \Nmy first time staying in a hotel."
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.57,0:57:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,"I can hardly describe it!"
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.87,0:57:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,"The play of Hamlet was much more interesting than the book."
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.86,0:57:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Judy?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.98,0:57:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I never knew they \Nserved food on trains.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.95,0:57:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Where on earth \Nwere you raised?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.17,0:57:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,A village, but there weren't too many people there.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.82,0:57:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If you didn't know trains served food, \Ndid you not go on holiday?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.83,0:58:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,My first time was \Ngoing to university.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.07,0:58:16.47,Default,,30,30,0,,{\fscx95}"Susan always thought I was a bit strange because I sometimes say such odd things."
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.85,0:58:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,"I was so overwhelmed by everything in New York...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.84,0:58:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that I blurted out it was my first time seeing a dining car."
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.12,0:58:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,"Having spent 17 \Nyears in an orphanage,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.70,0:58:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,experiences like these would \Nmake anyone's head spin."
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.26,0:58:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.81,0:58:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,My uncle seems to have \Ntaken an interest in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.55,0:58:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think so, Sally?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.99,0:58:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he was talking to Judy a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.64,0:59:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess the rumors about him hating women aren't true after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.39,0:59:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,"Honestly, even without Susan saying anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.80,0:59:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I already knew that Jervis \Nfelt this way about me."
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.76,0:59:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,"Some things don't need to be said to be understood, do they?"
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.86,0:59:20.68,Default,,30,30,0,,{\fscx95}"P.S. I'm amazed you've spent the last year living in the hustle and bustle of New York."
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.84,0:59:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,"But I'd recommend going out into the country once in a while."
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.02,0:59:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,"Given your age and all."
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.46,0:59:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Over the summer, she's to go to \Nthe Rock Willow Farm in Connecticut.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.31,0:59:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.96,0:59:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it hasn't come yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.64,0:59:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.63,0:59:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Judy, would you like to \Nspend summer at our family villa?{can't make out the bit after "uchi no" - kinda guesstimating on context}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.87,0:59:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Your family's villa?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.91,0:59:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.47,0:59:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a real rustic place surrounded by lakes and forests.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.07,1:00:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother thinks \Nyou'll love it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.61,1:00:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So she'd love for you to come.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.29,1:00:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,My, that sounds lovely!\NI'd love to go!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.65,1:00:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And Tommy said he's coming \Nwith all his friends from university.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.20,1:00:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your chance \Nto get a boyfriend!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.90,1:00:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Sally.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.53,1:00:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, it's decided!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.94,1:00:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll let my mother \Nknow right away!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.66,1:00:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure Tommy will \Nbe pleased as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.37,1:00:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,My...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.89,1:00:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes, yes, yes.\N That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.86,1:00:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it says here that she's been \Ninvited to the McBride's villa.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.55,1:00:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, very well, \Nthe Rock Willow Farm it is then.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.15,1:00:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I understand. \NI'll see to it personally.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.90,1:00:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,"Dear, Daddy-Long-Legs,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.03,1:01:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be staying at the Rock Willow Farm over the summer, just like you asked."
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.93,1:01:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,"But... why? Why couldn't I spend time with Sally?"
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.89,1:01:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Judy, why can't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.43,1:01:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.42,1:01:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,My!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.23,1:01:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy, you already know \NYoung Master Jervis?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.86,1:01:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Young master?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.83,1:01:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how old he is,\N he's still the young master to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.10,1:01:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I nursed him when \Nhe was a child.{"wet nurse" is the term used.}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.05,1:01:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I never would've guessed.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.18,1:01:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.37,1:01:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, is Young Master \NJervis doing well?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.97,1:02:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. He seemed well when we met \Ntwo months ago in New York.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.03,1:02:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.55,1:02:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say it was when he \Nwas about 11 years old.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.40,1:02:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He caught pneumonia and ended \Nup staying here over the summer.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.90,1:02:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Young Master Jervis really is the most \Ndashing man in the Pendleton family.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.36,1:02:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,"Daddy-Long-Legs,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.01,1:02:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,could this really be a coincidence?"
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.32,1:02:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,"Or do you happen to know Jervis?"
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.92,1:02:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,"Did you hear of this \Nplace because of Jervis?"
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.60,1:03:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.27,1:03:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, almost.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.26,1:03:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeez!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.65,1:03:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,"This is a wonderful place."
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.34,1:03:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,"It's good for the soul."
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.70,1:03:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,"And I also got a letter from Sally."
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.07,1:03:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,"For Tommy's \Ngraduation present,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.50,1:03:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,they're going to go on a car trip, and they said they're going to come to the farm!"
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.57,1:03:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,"I can't wait!"
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.11,1:03:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,"To Daddy-Long-Legs, from Judy."
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.21,1:03:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.34,1:04:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Up you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.68,1:04:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,There I go.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.95,1:04:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- Wait, I've never done this before.\N- It'll be fine, this one's well-behaved.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.33,1:04:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Wait, hey.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.82,1:04:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,O-On second thoughts, \Nget me down.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.95,1:04:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Away you go!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.09,1:04:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Help me!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.38,1:04:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Young lady!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.94,1:04:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.56,1:04:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,A-Are you okay?!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.76,1:04:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.85,1:04:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,She doesn't seem in \Na bad way, does she?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.15,1:04:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, she's just sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.80,1:04:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But didn't she \Nfall off a horse?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.14,1:05:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't anything serious, \NYoung Master.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.45,1:05:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you stop with the "young master" thing, Laura?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.80,1:05:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with calling you \N"young master," Young Master?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.90,1:05:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, I hear you \Nfell off a horse?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.08,1:05:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Jervis...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.67,1:05:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd come and pay \NLaura a visit, and look who I find.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.45,1:05:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.98,1:06:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.34,1:06:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in your second year \Nof university, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.62,1:06:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.15,1:06:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The same year as Susan.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.66,1:06:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But we'll be in our \Nthird year soon.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.51,1:06:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you stay \Non at university?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.31,1:06:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.00,1:06:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you want \Nto see Europe?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.77,1:06:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Paris, Rome, Vienna.{unless "Wien" is better to use}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.11,1:06:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.74,1:06:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But that would \Nbe impossible for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.94,1:06:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What if someone paid \Nfor you to do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.58,1:06:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone is already paying \Nfor my university fees.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.47,1:06:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't possibly ask them \Nto pay for me to go to Europe.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.13,1:06:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you ever think of leaving \Nuniversity and traveling around Europe?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.09,1:06:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.63,1:06:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There's still a lot for me \Nto learn at university.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.46,1:07:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to make \Nmany more friends.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.33,1:07:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There's so much \Nmore I want to learn.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.91,1:07:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But couldn't you \Ndo that in Europe?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.36,1:07:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That looks like Tommy!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.03,1:07:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, it's Sally's brother!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.30,1:07:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,There can't be many people \Nwith a car around here.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.99,1:07:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He said he'd pay \Nme a visit on his trip!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.01,1:07:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Tommy!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.89,1:07:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.23,1:07:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to Europe! \NWill you come with me?!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.30,1:07:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Jervis...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.02,1:08:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you come to \NEurope with me?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.90,1:08:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I will continue \Nmy studies at university.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.25,1:08:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.93,1:08:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Tommy!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.85,1:08:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Tommy!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.82,1:08:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You look well, Judy!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.14,1:08:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.96,1:08:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{近頃おかしなことがある}Lately, something strange has been happening.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.67,1:08:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{妙に甘い気分で}I'm in an oddly sweet mood.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.43,1:09:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{吹く風や小川の水に語りかけてくなるんだ}I feel like talking to the blowing wind and the stream's clear water.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.08,1:09:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{いったいどうしたわけだろう}What on earth could be going on?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.12,1:09:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{こいつはジュディのせいなのか}Is this all Judy's doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.43,1:09:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{どうもどうも恋に似ている}It really does feel a \Nlot like being in love.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.29,1:09:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{甘い甘い気分不思議な気持}A sweet, sweet mood, \Nsuch a mysterious feeling.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.86,1:09:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{ジュディを見ているとよみがえる}When I look at Judy,\N it comes flooding back.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.07,1:10:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{あの懐かしい青春の不思議な気持}That nostalgic, \Nmysterious feeling of youth.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.71,1:10:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.06,1:10:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,My brother says he'll come to our graduation.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.62,1:10:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What a relief.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.29,1:10:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So, who did Susan call?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.17,1:10:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Her favourite uncle, \Nwho else?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.99,1:10:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Jervis Pendleton.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.15,1:10:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you inviting, Judy?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.77,1:10:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.52,1:10:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,"The graduation ceremony is three weeks from next Wednesday."
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.21,1:10:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'd love for you to come."
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.65,1:11:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,"If you don't end up coming, \NI'll have to hold a grudge against you."
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.70,1:11:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well, I'll begin reading the names of those who have graduated.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.96,1:11:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Grace Hudson.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.63,1:11:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,"Daddy-Long-Legs."
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.55,1:11:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,"I didn't think you'd turn up."
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.07,1:11:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Mary Stewart.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.51,1:11:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold still now.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.01,1:11:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.98,1:11:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,One, two, and...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.98,1:11:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Three!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.13,1:11:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,"I graduated university."
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.73,1:11:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,"Tommy came to \Nthe graduation ceremony,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.49,1:11:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but Mr. Jervis, invited by Susan,\N was too sick to attend."
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.95,1:11:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Number 532 to \NNew York please.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.51,1:12:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, is this the \NPendleton household?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.85,1:12:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'm on my way back \Nto Rock Willow Farm."
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.06,1:12:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'd planned on writing a novel here over the summer."
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.32,1:12:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,"But my heart isn't in it and I can't seem to focus."
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.49,1:12:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,"I've wanted to talk to you for a long time now."
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.49,1:12:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,"About Mr. Jervis."
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.51,1:12:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,"When Susan told me he was unwell,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.73,1:12:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew I had to visit him."
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.39,1:12:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,"If only I could see his face."
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.36,1:13:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,"I don't know why I \Nfeel this way about him."
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.67,1:13:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"Daddy-Long-Legs."
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.68,1:13:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"Please, would you give me permission to visit Jervis Pendleton?"
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.12,1:13:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,"To Daddy-Long-Legs, \Nfrom Judy, a girl lost in love."
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.77,1:13:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy! Judy!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.79,1:13:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,A letter's come for you!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.26,1:13:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.81,1:13:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.82,1:13:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.49,1:13:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's from Daddy-Long-Legs!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.83,1:14:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'll meet you next Wednesday at 4:30 pm - Daddy-Long-Legs."
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.42,1:14:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooray! \NI finally get to meet him!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.05,1:14:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooray!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.29,1:14:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.18,1:14:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, but it's okay, I've been \Nto New York three times now.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.50,1:14:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Henry.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.08,1:14:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Judy.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.43,1:14:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem in \Ngood spirits, Judy.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.34,1:14:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Giddy-up!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.87,1:14:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be back soon!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.99,1:14:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Your boyfriend waiting \Nfor you in New York?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.73,1:14:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,My boyfriend?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.71,1:14:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.03,1:15:03.73,Default,,30,30,0,,{\fscx95}That's right. I finally get to meet the man I've been thinking of for the past four years.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.93,1:15:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.96,1:15:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Griggs!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.31,1:15:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, your carriage awaits.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.82,1:15:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.40,1:16:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I-Is Daddy-Long-Legs \Nan older gentleman?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.43,1:16:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he older than you? \NOr perhaps younger?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.87,1:16:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he bald?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.38,1:16:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Or does he have gray hair?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.34,1:16:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see when you meet him.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.84,1:16:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely, he must have children?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.93,1:16:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Or maybe even \Ngrandchildren?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.75,1:16:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You can ask him yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.07,1:17:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he know Mr. Pendleton?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.86,1:17:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he know \NJervis Pendleton?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.80,1:17:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I wouldn't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.43,1:17:17.29,Default,,30,30,0,,{\fscx95}They're both wealthy and live in New York,\N so they must know one another.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.29,1:17:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, who is to say?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.63,1:18:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Abbott, I assume?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.13,1:18:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.97,1:18:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll show you to the master. Right this way, Young Lady.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.23,1:18:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The master hasn't been well of late, \Nso he has been confined to his bed.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.01,1:18:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,My...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.64,1:18:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.31,1:19:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He's through here.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.59,1:19:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Abbott is here to see you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.26,1:19:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Judy Abbott, \NDaddy-Long-Legs.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.98,1:19:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I've... I've wanted to \Nmeet you for so long!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.14,1:19:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy-Long-Legs?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.81,1:20:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy, didn't you realize \NI was Daddy-Long-Legs?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.46,1:20:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Jervis...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.49,1:20:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You were Jervis?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.36,1:20:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You were Daddy-Long-Legs?!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.78,1:20:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Jervis!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.15,1:20:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.51,1:20:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.53,1:21:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy, Daddy-Long-Legs.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.86,1:21:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{あなたなのねあしながおじさん}It was you all along, \NDaddy-Long-Legs.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.38,1:21:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy, Daddy-Long-Legs.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.90,1:21:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{そうです僕があしながおじさん}Yes, it's me, I'm Daddy-Long-Legs.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.71,1:21:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{さがしてたひとはあなた}The one I was \Nsearching for was you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.37,1:21:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(Daddy-Long-Legs. Daddy-Long-Legs.)
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.63,1:21:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{このめぐり逢いこそすべて}This meeting means everything to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.61,1:21:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(Daddy-Long-Legs. Daddy-Long-Legs.)
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.57,1:21:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{夢ならさめないで}If this is a dream, \Ndon't let me wake up.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.14,1:21:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{あなたのおそばにいることがわたしの望みと今わかるの}Now I know being by your side is my only wish.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.79,1:22:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy-Long-Legs. Daddy-Long-Legs.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.92,1:22:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy, Daddy-Long-Legs.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.28,1:22:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{あなたなのねあしながおじさん}It was you all along,\N Daddy-Long-Legs.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.82,1:22:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy, Daddy-Long-Legs.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.29,1:22:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{そうです僕があしながおじさん}Yes, it's me,\N I'm Daddy-Long-Legs.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.21,1:22:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold in your warm arms...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.06,1:22:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(Daddy-Long-Legs. Daddy-Long-Legs.)
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.98,1:22:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{踊る夢をみてたいつも}I always dreamed of dancing with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.97,1:22:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(Daddy-Long-Legs. Daddy-Long-Legs.)
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.02,1:23:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{こうして逢えたのはふたりの心が求め合いひとつになるのを願ったから}We could only meet like this because our hearts longed for each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.18,1:23:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy-Long-Legs. Daddy-Long-Legs.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.85,1:23:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{愛のきらめきよ}The sparkle of love.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.22,1:23:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy-Long-Legs. Daddy-Long-Legs.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.02,1:23:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{愛のよろこびいつまでも}The joy of love, forevermore.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.03,1:23:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\blur1\fs80\pos(733.66,910.67)\c&HFCFBFF&}@InkaSubs
